children.content: 1. DToS will run share administration services with Service Providers. We should have the ability to do it centrally, shared, or just locally. 2. DToS will facilitate a Shared Appointment Slot Calendar that will allow Service Poriders to manage slots locally and DToS to manage slots nationally. 2. Service Providers wil be commissined to provide SEM focused services 3. DToS will provide interfaces to Service Providers so that DToS servceos can be used through local systems (eg EPRs, GP Systems, LIMS etc) 4. DToS will allocate Particpants to Screening Slots and will faciltate the interactions with Participants 5. DToS will maintain a virtual Screening Call Centre. This will be used by one or more central teams providing mainline and overflow facilities. Local services can use the Call Center facilities to provide locally-focused responses.
Principles for this Model in its final state (Post Release 3)

This tower provides the means to allocate participants to slots (for appointment based programmes) and equivalent in other programmes. It syncs the DToS calendar with Service Provider calendars to provide a soltuion for national/local app't mgmt. It provides the control mechanisms for multi-channel 2-way mgmt of participant interaction.
This tower manages the Next Best action after SEMs and will facilitate the future action for the participant. Addditionally, referral and outcome mgmt.

This tower is mainly about forward planning at the Screening Committee level. What are the new modalities ? Have they been proven? What are the dimensions of a future screening programme? There is probably a lot of data anlaysis but with little formal supporting systems.

This tower is to provide the means to engage with UK citizens with screening. This is marketing, promotion etc ahead, during and after citizens have engaged with screening. When citizens engagement and want to convert to participants, they are passed to Service Planning

This tower gathers the full cohort for each screening programme (the Demand) and manages the subsequent Supply side capacity. The change to current process is it does this by understanding the demand from a participant point of view not a Service Provider point of view. It does not attmpt to allocate Partcipants to Service Providers. However, to honour existing processes (for Release 0) this tower can also allocate participants to Service Providers in advance of slot alloctation.

This tower manages the Screenign Event by modality and programme (ie there are multiple SEMs for Breast Screening: Mammography, Biopsy, Ultrasound). The tower starts at arrive at a screening location (a BSO (for breast), or bathroom (for bowel). It encompases logistics of moving test samples (electronically or physically) to a examination capability or lab. It ends when that modality assessment has been completed and has a formal observation.

Capacity Models: > Free Capacity - Based on unlimited capacity per location - with cohort allocted using defined rules - in order to assess an ideal allocation. > Planned Capacity - A Service Provider will have a planned capacity that it expects to be able to provide (this will be based on historic capacity, commissioned capacity and/or Free capacity. > Actual Capacity - This is capcity that the SErvice Provider has promised to provide.
